WEBVTT

00:01.067 --> 00:02.796
Myname is Michael Westen.

00:02.869 --> 00:05.531
I used to be a spy until--

00:05.605 --> 00:08.096
- [ Man ] We got a burn notice on you.
You're blacklisted.
- [ Whistles ]

00:08.173 --> 00:10.574
[ Michael Narrating]
Whenyou're burned,you've got nothing--

00:10.643 --> 00:13.203
no cash, no credit,
nojob history.

00:13.279 --> 00:16.407
- You're stuck in whatever city
they decide to dump you in.
- Where am I?

00:16.483 --> 00:18.110
Miami.

00:18.184 --> 00:20.812
You do whatever work
comes your way.

00:20.887 --> 00:23.879
- You rely on anyone who's still talking to you--
- [ Laughs ]

00:23.957 --> 00:26.482
- a trigger-happy ex-girlfriend--
- Should we shoot them?

00:26.559 --> 00:29.392
an old friend who's informing
on you to the F..B.I.--

00:29.462 --> 00:31.760
You know spies.
Bunch of bitchy little girls.

00:31.831 --> 00:34.163
- F.amily too--
- Hey, is that your mom again?

00:34.234 --> 00:36.395
- ifyou're desperate.
- Someone needs your help, Michael.

00:36.469 --> 00:38.801
Bottom line:
Untilyou figure out who burnedyou...

00:40.974 --> 00:42.965
you're not going anywhere.

00:49.315 --> 00:51.806
[ Grunting ]

00:56.656 --> 00:59.853
- [ Gun Cocks ]
- Whoa! Mike, easy.

00:59.926 --> 01:02.190
- That'll kill you, you know.
- Yeah, no kiddin'.

01:02.262 --> 01:04.321
No, the bucket of
trans fat you got there.

01:04.397 --> 01:07.764
Did Veronica call you? 'Cause ifyou're
taking her side on this whole cholesterol thing...

01:07.834 --> 01:10.200
it's gonna put a serious strain
on our friendship.

01:10.270 --> 01:12.761
- No, you can binge in peace, Sam.
- Yeah, well, thanks.

01:12.839 --> 01:16.468
But that's not the only reason
why I'm here, you know. I got a job offer.

01:19.479 --> 01:22.812
Uh, here we go.
Pete-- one of my buddies from the SEAL teams--

01:22.882 --> 01:24.816
he's got a lady
who's got some problems.

01:24.884 --> 01:27.910
She called him 'cause he's in Special Forces.
But he's got this blood pressure thing...

01:27.987 --> 01:29.921
so he called me.

01:29.989 --> 01:32.219
- What doyou say?
- My plate's a little full, Sam.

01:32.292 --> 01:34.317
What, you mean with this
whole Philip Cowan thing?

01:34.394 --> 01:36.828
Mike, you're doing armed sit-ups.
I'm worried aboutyou.

01:36.896 --> 01:39.922
- I thought this might getyour mind offit.
- Cowan burned me.

01:39.999 --> 01:43.127
Cowan sent someone to kill me.
Now he dropped off grid.

01:43.203 --> 01:45.797
- I need my mind focused on this.
- All right. Fair enough.

01:45.872 --> 01:49.205
- You mind ifl run with this? The money's not bad.
- No. Knockyourself out.

01:49.275 --> 01:51.209
All right.

01:54.147 --> 01:57.048
[ Cell Phone Beeps ]

01:59.452 --> 02:01.579
What's that?

02:01.654 --> 02:04.248
- [ Sighs ]
- Well, it looks likeyour buddy Cowan
finally made contact.

02:04.324 --> 02:06.258
You want me to come with,
backyou up?

02:06.326 --> 02:09.523
- Sure. Bring your bucket offat.
- I'll bring my chicken too.

02:09.596 --> 02:11.530
Oh, yeah.

02:19.339 --> 02:23.742
[ Cell Phone Ringing]

02:23.810 --> 02:26.438
- Yeah, Sam.
- Well, it's the witching hour.

02:26.513 --> 02:30.210
- Looks likeyour buddy didn't show.
- He wouldn't just not show up.

02:30.283 --> 02:32.342
- He's watching.
- You think?

02:33.653 --> 02:36.019
Where doyou think
hewould be?

02:36.089 --> 02:39.024
I know where I'd be.

02:39.092 --> 02:40.684
[ Cell Phone Beeps ]

02:42.000 --> 02:48.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

03:28.641 --> 03:30.336
- [ CarDoorCloses ]
- [ CarDeparts ]

03:35.148 --> 03:37.639
- What doyou think he wants, Mike?
- Think he wants to meet.

03:37.717 --> 03:39.742
- So why not just meet?
- He doesn't trust me.

03:39.819 --> 03:41.980
F.air enough.
I don't trust him.

03:42.055 --> 03:45.183
[ Michael Narrating]
The first step in dealing with a covert op...

03:45.258 --> 03:48.250
is establishing a way
to communicate privately, a code.

03:48.328 --> 03:51.422
Could be a key-encrypted cipher.
But, really...

03:51.497 --> 03:53.795
allyou need is a base
ofknowledge thatyou share.

03:53.866 --> 03:57.131
He knows my enti re career--
falsified a good bit of it.

03:57.203 --> 04:00.639
It shouldn't be too difficult for him
to figure out a way to talk to me.

04:00.707 --> 04:04.609
Ah, the mating dance of the spy.

04:04.677 --> 04:07.942
It's a wonder spies everget close enough
to kill each other, isn't it?

04:08.014 --> 04:11.711
- Oh, gotta go.
- Veronica has you on a pretty tight leash, huh?

04:11.784 --> 04:14.150
Hardy-har.
I'm meeting with a prospective client.

04:14.220 --> 04:16.882
Mike, buddy, you call me
ifyou need anything.

04:16.956 --> 04:19.925
Fiona,just keep doin'
whatever it is you do.

04:34.407 --> 04:37.740
Thanks for meeting me.
I-- I thought there were two ofyou.

04:37.810 --> 04:41.211
Uh, yeah, usually, but my partner's
on somethin' else right now. But it's fine.

04:43.149 --> 04:46.710
So, um, Pete says
you're having some trouble?

04:46.786 --> 04:49.152
Uh, I'm a supervisor at S.X.G.

04:49.222 --> 04:54.319
We build planes, satellites, weapons systems.
Government contracts.

04:54.394 --> 04:58.353
Been working there 1 0 years.
It's a good job.

04:58.431 --> 05:00.899
- Areyou okay?
- I--

05:00.967 --> 05:03.663
Look, it's okay.
I'm like a doctor or a lawyer.

05:03.736 --> 05:06.136
Well, not a lawyer.
But the point is...

05:06.205 --> 05:09.697
you can tell me whateveryou want,
just between the two of us.

05:09.776 --> 05:14.338
My friend Melissa--we work together.
She was having an affair.

05:14.414 --> 05:18.214
Herhusband, Kent,
is abusive, controlling.

05:18.284 --> 05:20.582
The only time she has alone
is at the office.

05:20.653 --> 05:24.783
But to sign in guests,
you have to have security clearance, so--

05:24.857 --> 05:28.054
So you did her a favor.

05:30.096 --> 05:33.862
Her boyfriend stole files...

05:33.933 --> 05:37.096
took photos of them together
in the building.

05:37.170 --> 05:41.800
I'm the one who signed him in.
I could lose my clearance, myjob, go to jail even.

05:41.874 --> 05:45.002
- He's blackmailing us.
- What does this guywant from you?

05:45.078 --> 05:48.309
I have to sign forpackages,
and Melissa smuggles them out.

05:48.381 --> 05:51.407
Any idea what's in
these packages?

05:51.484 --> 05:55.750
They're from a subsidiary of S.X.G. in Turkey.

05:55.822 --> 05:58.620
I checked one.
It's-- It's drugs.

05:58.691 --> 06:02.821
- I don't know what kind.
- Well, that part ofthe world, it's probably heroin.

06:04.397 --> 06:07.332
There's another one
coming in this week.

06:07.400 --> 06:10.767
- I just want to get out.
- I'll see what I can do.

06:12.305 --> 06:15.069
I-I-- I don't want help.

06:15.141 --> 06:18.235
I-- I want to keep my secret.
I have to.

06:18.311 --> 06:21.075
I don't want to get anybody in trouble.
I'm not here to judge.

06:21.147 --> 06:25.140
I've made plenty of mistakes myself,
God only knows. [ Chuckles ]

06:25.218 --> 06:27.709
Listen. I was lonely.

06:27.787 --> 06:29.812
And Dave was--
I made a mistake.

06:29.889 --> 06:31.823
I just-- I want to
put it behind me.

06:31.891 --> 06:33.415
Okay. Dave--

06:33.493 --> 06:36.189
Uh, Gillian was saying thatyou
met this Dave at a bar.

06:36.262 --> 06:38.321
Which one?

06:38.398 --> 06:40.662
I don't know.
I-- I don't-- I don't remember.

06:40.733 --> 06:44.100
Myhusband's home.
Come on, please. You have to go.

06:44.170 --> 06:47.230
Okay. You know how
to get ahold of me.

06:49.308 --> 06:53.540
Don't worry about it.
We'll just fill in the blanks ourselves, I guess.

06:53.613 --> 06:58.448
Now, listen, when was the first time Melissa
ever talked about her new friend Dave?

07:01.020 --> 07:03.716
Mom? I got here as fast as I could.
What's the problem?

07:03.790 --> 07:06.122
I got a phone call, Michael.
I was scared.

07:06.192 --> 07:09.161
- Phone call? What kind of phone call?
- It was foryou. Some man.

07:09.228 --> 07:11.958
He wouldn't leave his name
or his number-- nothing.

07:12.031 --> 07:15.899
All he said was, "Van Buren Avenue,"
and then he hangs up.

07:15.968 --> 07:18.801
- What's that supposed to mean?
- Oh, it was probablyjust a friend.

07:18.871 --> 07:22.398
That isn't how friends behave, Michael.
All right?

07:22.475 --> 07:24.409
The way he said it scared me.

07:24.477 --> 07:27.037
- [ Clattering]
- Ow! Michael!

07:28.214 --> 07:30.341
[Knocking]

07:30.416 --> 07:33.214
[Nate ]
Ma? I lost mykey.

07:33.286 --> 07:35.311
- [ Banging]
- Worried it was your friend?

07:38.624 --> 07:41.923
Hey, Bro.
You look tired.

07:41.994 --> 07:45.361
Hey, Nate. You look clean.
You shaved the ferret offyour face.

07:48.668 --> 07:52.536
So what couldn't wait, Ma?
I had to walk out on a really big investor.

07:52.605 --> 07:54.266
What doyou mean by investor?

07:54.340 --> 07:57.776
Yeah, a buddyofmine, he's got a process
that recycles titanium golfclubs.

07:57.844 --> 08:00.608
It's gonna totally
revolutionize the golfclub--

08:00.680 --> 08:03.547
- Forget it.
- Mom, why did you call Nate?

08:03.616 --> 08:06.016
I called your brother too
because I was scared.

08:06.085 --> 08:08.053
What's goin' on here?

08:08.120 --> 08:10.281
A strange man phoned here.

08:10.356 --> 08:13.018
Michael won't tell me anything about him
because it's all a big mystery.

08:13.092 --> 08:16.323
It's just better ifl don't get into it.
Trust me. I know what I'm doing.

08:16.395 --> 08:20.024
There's nothing to worryabout.
This man who called-- hejust wants to talk.

08:20.099 --> 08:23.262
But you can't talk to us?

08:23.336 --> 08:26.237
You know, in 20years, Michael,
I have never asked any questions.

08:26.305 --> 08:28.239
But this is my home.

08:28.307 --> 08:31.799
It's not like it's some war off
in some country that I've never even heard of.

08:31.878 --> 08:34.711
This-- This is your family.

08:34.780 --> 08:36.714
Oh, I know.

08:39.418 --> 08:41.544
- [ Door Opens ]
- [ Mouths Word ]

08:41.621 --> 08:43.885
- [ Door Closes ]
- Okay. You can tell me.

08:43.956 --> 08:45.890
Seriously, what's goin' on here?

08:45.958 --> 08:48.825
Nate, I need you to watch Mom.
It's just a precaution.

08:48.895 --> 08:52.729
I need you to lay low for a while.
Keep a low profile.

08:52.798 --> 08:55.460
Don't leave the house.
You can do that, right?

08:59.906 --> 09:01.840
- Yeah.
- Safety's off.

09:02.909 --> 09:04.968
[ Chuckles ]

09:05.044 --> 09:07.308
Course, I--you know,
I will be taking time offwork...

09:07.380 --> 09:11.009
and I'll need to get some,
you know, supplies...

09:11.083 --> 09:14.484
in case things
get dicey around here.

09:14.554 --> 09:16.818
Recycled titanium, huh?

09:16.889 --> 09:19.119
What is that, a name of a horse?

09:24.697 --> 09:26.824
Well, Fiona.

09:26.899 --> 09:30.528
Hey, how you doin'?
Thanks for comin'.

09:30.603 --> 09:32.935
Wow, you look great.
Sit down.

09:33.005 --> 09:37.806
- [ Sighs ]
- So, to what do I owe
the pleasure ofthis invitation?

09:37.877 --> 09:41.904
- Am I to beyour new drinking buddy?
- Ah-- [ Chuckles ] Yeah.

09:41.981 --> 09:44.779
Uh, it's this job that I'm on--
I need some backup.

09:44.850 --> 09:47.944
And Mike's mind is pretty much
on this whole Cowan business. So I thought--

09:48.020 --> 09:51.012
Of me.

09:51.090 --> 09:53.991
I thought ofyou.
Yes, that's what I thought.

09:54.060 --> 09:56.722
- [ Chuckles ]
- What's the job?

09:56.796 --> 09:58.627
Well, it's a blackmail thing.

09:58.698 --> 10:02.190
And one ofthe victims got spooked,
so she's not saying where she met the bad guy.

10:02.268 --> 10:04.395
But I think I got enough
to put it together.

10:04.470 --> 10:08.201
She met him out at a bar,
and I have an approximate date.

10:11.077 --> 10:14.513
- That's not much to go on.
- I got a guywho's pulling
her credit card statement.

10:14.580 --> 10:17.572
Find the charge,
find the bar, find the guy.

10:17.650 --> 10:20.881
- And you need a wingman.
- Damn straight, skippy.

10:20.953 --> 10:24.821
My fee is 500 up front, expenses,
and an hourly as we go.

10:24.890 --> 10:27.984
- You never charge Mike.
- Oh, I expect other things from Michael.

10:33.532 --> 10:36.262
[ Cell Phone Ringing]

10:36.335 --> 10:39.532
- Yeah, Fi.
- Sam just hired me for a job.

10:39.605 --> 10:41.539
I thought he was gonna be ill.

10:41.607 --> 10:45.202
It was so much fun, Michael.
I wishyou could have been there.

10:45.277 --> 10:48.508
Cowan sent me a message.
I'm searching the cafÃ©s of South Beach for a cutout.

10:48.581 --> 10:52.108
Don't you think he'll come himself?
He seems eager to meet you.

10:52.184 --> 10:54.118
[ Michael]
I doubt it. He'll sendsomeone.

10:54.186 --> 10:59.055
I did something similar in Belgradeyears ago.
Long story.

10:59.125 --> 11:02.754
[F.iona ] Have fun. There's a reason
I neverhad the patience to be a spy.

11:02.828 --> 11:04.819
All right.

11:04.897 --> 11:07.525
[ Michael Narrating] The trulyparanoid
don't go to meetings themselves.

11:07.600 --> 11:10.433
They use a cutout--
someone unrelated to them...

11:10.503 --> 11:13.529
hired to show a prearranged sign
and deliver a message.

11:13.606 --> 11:18.236
The sign is something innocuous
but hard to miss.

11:18.310 --> 11:21.279
My favorite is the tourist guide
for Madison, Wisconsin.

11:21.347 --> 11:23.838
No one will look at it twice...

11:23.916 --> 11:25.884
but unless I'm in the Midwest...

11:25.951 --> 11:28.419
I know they're waiting
for Michael Westen.

11:28.487 --> 11:30.455
- You here for the envelope?
- Who are you?

11:30.523 --> 11:32.457
[ Scoffs ]
Ain't nobody, man.

11:32.525 --> 11:34.459
Look, some guy gives me a hundred bucks.

11:34.527 --> 11:37.826
He says give this to the first guy
that comes by and bugs me.

11:37.897 --> 11:39.831
You are buggin' me.

11:57.149 --> 12:01.483
- ??[Ambient, F.aint]
- [ Chattering ]

12:03.489 --> 12:05.480
So this is where
Melissa met her boyfriend.

12:06.992 --> 12:10.291
Seems a little unlikely.
But she definitelypaid for drinks here.

12:10.362 --> 12:12.387
How do you want
to handle this?

12:14.600 --> 12:17.569
- Well, I think the balls are in your court.
- Oh, great.

12:17.636 --> 12:19.695
The hell am I
paying you for anyway?

12:21.107 --> 12:24.235
Hey, how you doin'?
Um, I'm looking for a friend of mine.

12:24.310 --> 12:26.335
Just want to see
ifyou can help me out.

12:26.412 --> 12:28.642
Handsome guy right there.

12:28.714 --> 12:31.808
Hey. Howyou guys doin'?
[ Clears Throat ]

12:31.884 --> 12:34.614
How about those Dolphins, huh?
[ Chuckling ]

12:38.057 --> 12:41.857
- So how did we do?
- Well, uh, my new friends have informed me...

12:41.927 --> 12:46.387
that the mysterious Dave is actually
a hustler named RayWagoner.

12:46.465 --> 12:51.198
So he was just stepping up to the exciting world
ofblackmail and smack dealing.

12:51.270 --> 12:55.673
Yeah. I guess he's broken a few hearts
and lifted a few wallets here.

12:55.741 --> 12:59.837
- But I have his address.
- You know, Sam, I have to say...

12:59.912 --> 13:01.846
you were captivating
over there.

13:01.914 --> 13:05.372
[ Chuckling ]
Well, hey, a free drink is a free drink, baby.

13:05.451 --> 13:07.885
They liked the shirt.

13:15.127 --> 13:18.722
??[Rock, F.aint]

13:36.649 --> 13:38.116
[ Grunts ]

13:38.184 --> 13:40.209
[Board Clatters ]

13:43.522 --> 13:45.649
That's not a very nice way
to say hello.

13:45.724 --> 13:48.022
Let's try that again.
I'm Sam.

13:48.093 --> 13:50.891
- Now you say, "Hi, I'm Ray."
- What do you want?

13:52.364 --> 13:57.199
[ Sighs ] We want you
to find a new way to import your heroin.

13:57.269 --> 13:58.003
I seriously don't know
whatyou're talkin' about.

13:58.003 --> 14:01.700
I seriously don't know
whatyou're talkin' about.

14:01.774 --> 14:04.265
Gillian Walsh,
Melissa Fontenot--

14:05.511 --> 14:08.241
- You'regonna leave 'em alone.
- Her?

14:08.314 --> 14:11.613
I never messed with her.
We went on a couple dates.

14:11.684 --> 14:15.245
All she everwanted to do was take pictures
in some building. Hundred bucks a shot.

14:15.321 --> 14:17.312
She took the pictures?

14:17.389 --> 14:20.256
Yeah, and her husband paid.
Some guy-- flattop.

14:20.326 --> 14:24.285
It was weird.
I didn't ask questions.

14:24.363 --> 14:26.661
[ Sighs ]

14:27.666 --> 14:29.896
[ Sam ]
Melissa lied to us.

14:29.969 --> 14:32.563
- I knew it.
- You did not.

14:32.638 --> 14:35.903
- I suspected.
- Suspected doesn't count.

14:35.975 --> 14:37.909
We gotta talk to Mike.

14:40.212 --> 14:45.047
Ifshe was setting me up, whywould she be
in the photos? Why not just steal the files?

14:45.117 --> 14:48.018
[ Chuckling ] Well, she's the only one
who could get the packages out.

14:48.087 --> 14:52.524
If Melissa wasn't being "blackmailed,"
you'd know that she was in on it.

14:52.591 --> 14:56.083
Oh, my God.
I-I can't believe I fell for this.

14:56.161 --> 14:58.527
Don't be so hard onyourself.
Double blackmail's a classic.

14:58.597 --> 15:00.531
It's as old as the pyramids,
you know.

15:00.599 --> 15:04.035
You pose as a fellow target
ofyour own blackmail scheme.

15:04.103 --> 15:06.333
That way, you'll always know
what the victims are up to.

15:06.405 --> 15:09.966
- Pros use it all the time.
- So what do we do?

15:10.042 --> 15:13.534
We gotta get near Kent. Ifwe can
get some evidence linking him to the heroin...

15:13.612 --> 15:15.944
we can do our own blackmail,
get you off the hook.

15:16.015 --> 15:18.006
You know, start fighting
fire with fire.

15:18.083 --> 15:20.017
But Melissa knows I hired you.

15:20.085 --> 15:22.781
We'll have to make her think
that the investigation's stalled.

15:22.855 --> 15:26.814
Plus, we're gonna get some more help--
a little relieffrom the bullpen.

15:26.892 --> 15:30.225
Well, dowhateveryou need to do.
I'll pay more. I'll dip into my savings.

15:30.296 --> 15:32.560
Don'tworry
about the money, Gillian.

15:32.631 --> 15:35.122
We gotcha covered.

15:44.873 --> 15:48.832
- Hey, Mike. She runnin' again?
- More or less.

15:48.910 --> 15:51.105
How's your dance
with Cowan goin'?

15:51.179 --> 15:54.740
[ Sighs ] I don't know. It's hard to trust someone
under these circumstances.

15:54.816 --> 15:56.750
But I don't have a choice, do I?

15:56.818 --> 16:00.083
That part ofthe job, I don't miss it.
You guys set a meet yet?

16:00.155 --> 16:03.750
I think so. He sent an article
about a job I did in Budapest.

16:03.825 --> 16:06.419
I met a contact there
under the steps of city hall.

16:06.495 --> 16:08.929
- I assume that's where he wants to meet.
- Wow.

16:08.997 --> 16:10.988
Cowan gets the gold star
for clever, doesn't he?

16:11.066 --> 16:14.194
- Or he just likes watching
me run around in this heat.
- Want me to come with you?

16:14.269 --> 16:17.761
Thanks, but I think he wants
a little alone time with me.

16:17.839 --> 16:19.773
Ah.

16:19.841 --> 16:21.775
Yeah, hey.
Uh, listen, Mike.

16:21.843 --> 16:24.744
Um, this new client ofmine, Gillian--

16:24.813 --> 16:26.940
she's in kind ofa tough spot.

16:27.015 --> 16:29.882
I wasjustgiving her
a ride home, and, well, uh...

16:29.951 --> 16:34.047
there she is,
i-in my car right there.

16:34.122 --> 16:36.886
- Shameless, Sam. Even foryou.
- Look, Mike, I know you're busy.

16:36.958 --> 16:39.188
But I need a fresh face on this.

16:39.261 --> 16:42.924
It's a tiny little bit part. You'd be posing
as a Green Beret. Like falling off a log.

16:42.998 --> 16:44.932
What's the job?

16:45.000 --> 16:46.934
Well, it turns out
that Melissa's husband, Kent...

16:47.002 --> 16:48.936
is running all of
the smuggling down at S.X.G.

16:49.004 --> 16:52.997
