- [ Fiona ] Michael--
- Fi, can I call you back?

41:54.198 --> 41:56.223
Michael, Kent and Melissa's
deal went bad.

41:56.300 --> 42:00.794
- They're dead. And Sam--
- Whoa, whoa, whoa. What?
Slow down, Fi. Slow down.

42:00.871 --> 42:03.601
Kent's boss is cleaning house, I think.

42:03.674 --> 42:06.234
Theywere watching us.
They took Sam.

42:06.310 --> 42:09.040
- Who did?
- I don't know.
Whoever they are, they're damn good.

42:09.113 --> 42:11.877
- Where areyou, Fi?
- I can't talk.

42:11.949 --> 42:16.283
[ Sighs ] I'm in the warehouse district
by the First Street Bridge.

42:16.354 --> 42:19.414
- [Tires Squealing]
- They're coming.

42:37.007 --> 42:40.943
- You drop me off and you go. Got it?
- It's too late. You need me.

42:41.011 --> 42:43.605
Sam and Fi are dealing with heroin smugglers.
They already killed two people.

42:43.681 --> 42:46.241
Yeah. Sounds like
it's a bad time for me to bail.

42:46.317 --> 42:48.012
No, it's a perfect time
foryou to bail.

42:48.085 --> 42:50.986
Look, man, something happens toyou,
and Mom is on my ass forever.

42:51.055 --> 42:52.989
All right? Andnot to get
intoyourbusiness...

42:53.057 --> 42:55.582
but it seems like
you could use the help.

42:57.361 --> 42:59.488
Thankyou.

42:59.563 --> 43:02.964
You're welcome.
Family first, right?

43:05.002 --> 43:07.232
[Nate ]
She's in there somewhere?

43:10.608 --> 43:13.338
I mean, she could be in any one
ofthose buildings, man.

43:13.411 --> 43:15.345
She'll let us know
where she is.

43:15.413 --> 43:19.349
[Michael Narrating] In anyoperation,
communicating silentlyis often essential.

43:19.417 --> 43:22.682
Chalk marks,
an unusual arrangement ofobjects--

43:22.753 --> 43:25.381
anything that stands out
from the background will do.

43:25.456 --> 43:29.688
- A piece ofcloth on a window.
- There. She's there.

43:29.760 --> 43:33.127
Hmm. Great.
What are we gonna do about it?

43:33.197 --> 43:35.688
Those guys are all over
looking for her.

43:37.301 --> 43:39.667
I 'm gonna need to drive.

