52:45.841 --> 52:49.072
It's cold enough to crystallize the metal
in many commercial locks.

52:49.145 --> 52:51.079
A hammer can
take care ofthe rest.

52:52.815 --> 52:56.342
[ Fiona ]
So this is Sam's storage locker. Phew.

52:56.419 --> 52:59.183
[ Michael ]
We're looking for an old photo.

53:01.424 --> 53:04.757
It'll be from the mid-'90s
when we were working together.

53:04.827 --> 53:07.591
You really think Sam
is sending us a message?

53:07.663 --> 53:09.597
He's trying to get us
any information he can.

53:09.665 --> 53:12.759
It's the pose in the photo.
I've seen it before.

53:12.835 --> 53:14.894
[ Michael Narrating]
One advantage ofworking with the same team...

53:14.970 --> 53:17.632
is that secure communication
is simpler.

53:17.707 --> 53:19.641
You don't have to
work out a secret code.

53:19.709 --> 53:22.234
Ifyou have enough history,
the code is in everypicture...

53:22.311 --> 53:26.975
every memento,
every autographed leg cast.

53:27.049 --> 53:28.744
[ Sighs ]

53:30.019 --> 53:31.953
What is it?

53:35.391 --> 53:39.725
Sam led a hostage rescue operation
in Venezuela for some U.S. businessmen.

53:39.795 --> 53:43.128
It was a setup.
The hostages were bait forSam's team.

53:43.199 --> 53:46.191
He lost a few men.
He's saying stay away.

53:46.268 --> 53:48.202
He's not getting
out of this alive.

54:01.917 --> 54:05.318
- Good. You made it back. Was anyone there?
- Government types, Bro. Suits.

54:05.387 --> 54:09.517
There was a few plainclothes guys there too.
