- Oh,yeah.

54:17.767 --> 54:20.600
I drove around Little Haiti for an hour,
out to Virginia Key and back.

54:20.669 --> 54:24.002
It was a bitch and a half. But unless
they got invisible helicopters, I lost 'em.

54:24.073 --> 54:27.440
And the car. Did you leave the car
unattended when you went inside?

54:27.510 --> 54:30.775
- Don't worry. I ditched that car.
I picked up a new one.
- Uh-huh, stole it.

54:30.846 --> 54:34.304
It was, like, a 15-year-old Pontiac, Ma.
I did the guy a favor taking it.

54:34.383 --> 54:36.317
Point is we lost 'em.
We're clean.

54:36.385 --> 54:39.218
- You think they're the same guys that shot Cowan?
- Yeah.

54:39.288 --> 54:41.222
Michael, what is going on?

54:41.290 --> 54:44.851
I'm not sure. All I know is this isn't
just about following me anymore.

54:44.927 --> 54:48.158
- Theywant to bring me in.
- Who? Who is it? I don't know whatyou're talk--

54:48.230 --> 54:51.688
I don't know.
Covert intelligence agencies...

54:51.767 --> 54:54.327
don't call you up and tell you why
they're hunting you.

54:54.403 --> 54:57.304
Mom,just fornow,
I needyou to stayhere.

54:57.373 --> 55:00.365
No calls until I figure out
what's going on.

55:00.442 --> 55:03.172
- Here? Areyou serious?
- Mom,just until I know more.

55:03.245 --> 55:08.842
Nate, I need you to pick up some
disposable cell phones for emergencies only.

55:08.918 --> 55:11.580
- What areyou gonna do?
- Fi and I are gonna probe these guys...

55:11.654 --> 55:13.645
see how serious they are.

55:15.057 --> 55:18.185
Well, it's not a perfect location,
but it's not bad either.

55:18.260 --> 55:20.194
Just need something
nice and traceable--

55:20.262 --> 55:22.730
a trail that the guys
that killed Cowan can follow.

55:22.798 --> 55:24.732
- Whoyou gonna call?
- My old handler.

55:24.800 --> 55:27.564
Ifthey're not listening to his line,
they don't deserve to catch me.

55:27.636 --> 55:29.160
Hmm.

55:29.238 --> 55:32.571
[Beeping]

55:32.641 --> 55:34.734
[ Line Ringing ]

55:34.810 --> 55:36.801
Hi. Yes.
Dan Siebels, please.

55:36.879 --> 55:39.712
Oh, this is Michael Westen.
I need to talk to him. It's urgent.

55:39.782 --> 55:43.309
I have government agents following me--
I'm not surewhat agency they are.

55:43.385 --> 55:45.751
- But I need help. Could you send a helicopter?
- [ Line Clicks ]

55:45.821 --> 55:47.755
Okay. Good talking toyou too.

55:50.759 --> 55:53.284
[Michael Narrating]
Surveillance is a two-waystreet.

55:53.362 --> 55:56.229
Ifyou know someone's looking foryou,
you've got an advantage.

55:56.298 --> 55:59.563
They followyour lead,
go where they thinkyou are.

55:59.635 --> 56:02.433
Nice response time.
Ten minutes. They're good.

56:04.139 --> 56:06.539
Not that good.
They're staring at a pay phone.

56:08.510 --> 56:11.206
Oh, no, F.i.
They are that good.

56:11.280 --> 56:14.613
Those guys arejust to keep us busy.
They know we're here.

56:15.885 --> 56:18.410
[ Tires Squealing ]

56:20.222 --> 56:22.156
Tires.

56:24.627 --> 56:26.822
- It's armored.
- I 'll see you back at Nate's.

56:32.034 --> 56:33.968
[ Michael Narrating]
Who drives armored cars?

56:34.036 --> 56:36.266
People who expect gunfire.

56:36.338 --> 56:38.738
Usuallypeople
with some firepower oftheir own.

56:43.212 --> 56:44.941
[ Woman ]
Hey! What are you doing? Hey!

56:45.014 --> 56:47.073
- Sorry about that.
- What are you talkin' about?

56:47.149 --> 56:50.482
Hey, you!
Gimme my keys!

56:50.552 --> 56:53.180
[ Harrick ] You ready to talk about
how to getyour guySam back?

56:53.255 --> 56:55.849
- Yeah. You got a price?
- We'll get to that.

56:55.925 --> 56:58.519
First, I want to meet
you and the girl together.

56:58.594 --> 57:00.687
- The girl?
- You forgot already?

57:00.763 --> 57:03.596
Sure went through
a hell of a lot oftrouble to get her back.

57:03.666 --> 57:06.601
- She has nothing to do with this.
- She's part ofyour operation.

57:06.669 --> 57:09.968
I want to know who I'm dealing with.
Those are my conditions.

57:10.039 --> 57:13.497
Fine. But it's gonna take
a couple of days to track her down.

57:13.575 --> 57:16.635
- A couple ofdays?
- After what happened, she went underground.

57:16.712 --> 57:20.204
Ifyou want to see her,
you're gonna have to wait for me to find her.

57:20.282 --> 57:23.149
Don't take too long.
I'm not sure Sam can hold out.

57:23.218 --> 57:25.152
He's got decent stamina.

57:25.220 --> 57:27.756
But everyone's got a breaking point,
and I'm good at finding them.

57:27.756 --> 57:28.450
But everyone's got a breaking point,
and I'm good at finding them.

57:28.524 --> 57:31.982
[Michael Narrating] In a hostage situation,
you have to be cruel to be kind.

57:32.061 --> 57:34.689
The moreyou care,
the more leverage theyhave.

57:34.763 --> 57:38.494
Like buying a car--
you have to make them thinkyou can walk away.

57:38.567 --> 57:40.831
J ust so we're clear,
I don't take damaged goods.

57:40.903 --> 57:42.837
You break it, you buy it.
Got it?

57:42.905 --> 57:45.703
Call me whenyou find the girl.

57:46.809 --> 57:48.902
I take it
you just bought us more time.

57:48.978 --> 57:51.606
Won't do us much good
unless we find out who this guy is.

57:51.680 --> 57:55.548
All we know now is
he's got Sam and he intends to kill us.

57:55.617 --> 57:57.585
- Any ideas?
- Well, it's a pretty small world...

57:57.653 --> 57:59.587
when you're importing heroin
at that level.

57:59.655 --> 58:00.917
I'll make a call.

58:06.829 --> 58:09.024
Well, it's your lucky day.

58:09.098 --> 58:11.896
Your boss reallywants you back.
Guess that's loyalty foryou.

58:11.967 --> 58:14.993
You think he's gonna deal for me?
He's playin' with you.

58:15.070 --> 58:17.231
- Oh, really?
- Look, I got caught.

58:17.306 --> 58:20.332
He's gonna kill me himself.
Believe me, pal, you'd be doing me a big favor.

58:20.409 --> 58:23.276
- You got some death wish or somethin'?
- You're gonna do it anyway.

58:23.345 --> 58:27.247
What, I gotta stay another day
in this crappy metal box?

58:27.316 --> 58:29.284
Look, there's a sweet little park
in Coral Gables.

58:29.351 --> 58:32.377
Just dump the body.
Give me a piece of paper. I'll drawyou a map.

58:32.454 --> 58:34.251
Yap, yap, yap, yap, yap.

58:37.326 --> 58:40.818
He knows ifwe kill him
his team won't show.

58:40.896 --> 58:43.592
Nah. We need him alive.

58:43.665 --> 58:47.157
Fellas, you're only hurting yourselves.
I'm telling you.

58:47.236 --> 58:50.899
Come on. A little rat poison!
Easy-peasy!

58:50.973 --> 58:52.565
[ Sighs ]

58:53.709 --> 58:57.201
- Soyou want me to putyou
in touch with a heroin dealer?
- That is what I want.

58:57.279 --> 58:59.213
Look, heroin--
I'm allergic to it.

59:00.983 --> 59:03.008
Don't need to touch it,
don't need to see it.

59:03.085 --> 59:06.953
- I think about it, I get hives.
Heroin dealers-- seriously.
- This is not a favor.

59:07.022 --> 59:09.320
No, it's not.
Favors don't getyou killed.

59:09.391 --> 59:13.760
I giveyou a name, it gets back,
we're in a "Barry facedown in the river" situation.

59:13.829 --> 59:15.990
I'm not asking, Barry.

59:17.066 --> 59:19.864
We're friends
orwe're enemies here.

59:19.935 --> 59:22.836
Well, ifyou put it that way.

59:23.038 --> 59:24.630
I put it that way.

59:26.175 --> 59:29.008
[ Sighs ]
You want the biggest heroin dealer in Miami?

59:29.078 --> 59:31.376
This guy's as big as you say,
they're probablyworking together.

59:31.447 --> 59:33.506
No. Who's the second biggest?

59:33.582 --> 59:35.914
[ Muttering ]

59:35.984 --> 59:39.818
Mmm, there's this club
up on 22nd-- Deedo's.

59:39.888 --> 59:42.584
It's a place
usually for smack trade.

59:42.658 --> 59:45.218
You're looking for Carmelo.
He hangs out there...

59:45.294 --> 59:49.697
- does a lot ofbusiness in the V.I.P. room.
- [ Cell Phone Ringing]

59:51.533 --> 59:53.467
Yeah?

59:55.571 --> 59:57.505
Uh, Mike, it's foryou.

59:57.573 --> 59:59.541
Something about
your burn notice.

01:00:01.977 --> 01:00:05.344
-Y'ello.
-[ Woman ] Come out, come out, whereveryou are.

01:00:05.414 --> 01:00:07.507
- Who's this?
- We need to talk, Michael.

01:00:07.583 --> 01:00:09.517
We've been trying
to bring you in.

01:00:09.585 --> 01:00:12.486
- Talk about what?
- Your past, your future.

01:00:12.554 --> 01:00:15.921
Oh, sweetie, I'm a little busy right now.
Can you call me back?

01:00:16.054 --> 01:00:19.649
- Keep it. It's yours.
- [Splashes ]

01:00:21.726 --> 01:00:24.752
- We friends?
- We're friends, Barry.

01:00:43.048 --> 01:00:46.415
- Anything I can do to help in here?
- No, Mom. Please.

01:00:48.053 --> 01:00:51.682
We gotta get her to stop smokin', Bro.
She's making me nervous.

01:00:51.756 --> 01:00:54.657
- She just wants to help.
- She can help by making sandwiches.

01:00:54.726 --> 01:00:58.184
Making explosives,
areyou, Michael?

01:01:01.433 --> 01:01:05.164
Mom, there is some
serious business going on here.

01:01:05.236 --> 01:01:07.704
- I'm not stupid. I can see that.
- Look.

01:01:07.772 --> 01:01:10.366
I was hoping to getyou
back home in a couple of days...

01:01:10.442 --> 01:01:13.070
but that doesn't look like
it's gonna happen.

01:01:13.144 --> 01:01:15.704
What doyou mean?
I don't want to stayhere longer.

01:01:15.780 --> 01:01:18.578
I only brought a week's worth of clothes.
And I got a poker game tomorrow.

01:01:18.650 --> 01:01:20.743
No, Mom.
You're going to have to leave town.

01:01:20.819 --> 01:01:24.346
- Leave town?
- With Nate.

01:01:24.422 --> 01:01:26.754
No. I'm not going anywhere.
I'm staying here with you, Michael.

01:01:26.825 --> 01:01:29.259
- You're obviously in trouble.
- No, it's not safe. You can't.

01:01:29.327 --> 01:01:32.262
I don't care ifit's not safe here.
I'm not leaving you.

01:01:32.330 --> 01:01:34.890
- Mom, please.
- Michael, I'm not afraid.

01:01:34.966 --> 01:01:38.732
I knowyou're not afraid.
But I am.

01:01:40.171 --> 01:01:42.105
- Shh.
- [ Sighs ]

01:01:42.173 --> 01:01:44.641
It's okay.

01:01:47.679 --> 01:01:49.670
I'll go.

01:02:01.026 --> 01:02:04.223
??[Hip-hop]

01:02:11.403 --> 01:02:14.270
- ??[ Continues ]
- [ Beeps ]

01:02:19.811 --> 01:02:21.745
There's our man right there.

01:02:29.888 --> 01:02:33.085
- He looks like he's ready for trouble.
- I'll bring him trouble then.

01:02:33.158 --> 01:02:36.093
[Michael Narrating]
There are some fightsyoujust can't win.

01:02:36.161 --> 01:02:38.254
A force can be
so overwhelming...

01:02:38.329 --> 01:02:40.297
that no tactical approach in a fight...

01:02:40.365 --> 01:02:42.856
is going to lead
to a victory worth having.

01:02:42.934 --> 01:02:45.266
You sure you don't
want me to stay?

01:02:45.336 --> 01:02:48.794
No, Fi.
You need to go. Now.

01:02:48.873 --> 01:02:51.899
You know, I 'm usually all for the high risk,
high reward option.

01:02:51.976 --> 01:02:56.538
- But this--
- Ifthere was any otherway, believe me--

01:02:57.615 --> 01:02:59.549
Knock 'em dead.

01:03:03.455 --> 01:03:05.389
[Michael Narrating]
Whenyou can't win in a fight...

01:03:05.457 --> 01:03:09.416
sometimesyou have to settle formaking sure
that ifyou lose, everyone loses.

01:03:09.494 --> 01:03:12.190
It works for nuclear weapons,
it works for me.

01:03:13.932 --> 01:03:17.527
- Hey.
- Oh, sorry. Private party. My bad.

01:03:20.205 --> 01:03:22.730
[ Guns Cocking ]

01:03:22.807 --> 01:03:25.537
- You got a death wish, my friend.
- Back off.

01:03:26.878 --> 01:03:29.210
- What do you want?
- Send someone out into the club.

01:03:29.280 --> 01:03:31.612
I need them to check
under the bar, under the stairs...

01:03:31.683 --> 01:03:33.878
- under the chairs, for more ofthese.
- [ Beeps ]

01:03:33.952 --> 01:03:37.888
That's exactlywhat it looks like--
C-4 explosive with a remote detonator.

01:03:37.956 --> 01:03:40.720
[ Beeps ]

01:03:40.792 --> 01:03:42.726
And this--

01:03:44.195 --> 01:03:46.129
A remote detonator
on a deadman switch.

01:03:46.197 --> 01:03:48.495
You shoot me,
I let go ofthis button...

01:03:48.566 --> 01:03:51.535
and the city of Miami
gets some brand-new undeveloped real estate.

01:03:52.604 --> 01:03:53.935
[ Guns Clicking ]

01:03:54.005 --> 01:03:55.939
What doyou want?

01:03:56.007 --> 01:03:59.170
I just want to talk.
What areyou drinking?

01:04:01.513 --> 01:04:04.414
Champagne.
Would you like some?

01:04:04.482 --> 01:04:06.473
Please.

01:04:11.356 --> 01:04:13.756
Ooh, that's nice.
Little dry.

01:04:13.825 --> 01:04:16.521
- But sometimes dry is a little refreshing.
- Glad you like it.

01:04:16.594 --> 01:04:19.586
Thatwhyyou're here? Put a bomb
in my club soyou can drink my champagne?

01:04:19.664 --> 01:04:23.930
Partially. Also I need the name and location
ofa certain heroin importer.

01:04:24.002 --> 01:04:25.936
I need it quietly,
and I need it now.

01:04:26.004 --> 01:04:30.031
- [ Chuckles ] And I should do this because--
- Because he's an importer.

01:04:30.108 --> 01:04:32.042
He sells toyour competition.

01:04:32.110 --> 01:04:34.806
I put him out ofbusiness,
it's a win for both of us.

01:04:34.879 --> 01:04:37.404
And, ifyou don't
do what I want...

01:04:37.482 --> 01:04:41.316
I will rain hell down upon you
until one of us is dead.

01:04:41.386 --> 01:04:44.583
And I am really, really good
at raining down hell.

01:04:45.723 --> 01:04:47.850
I want an answer tomorrow.

01:04:49.794 --> 01:04:54.663
- Who areyou?
- I'm Michael Westen. I used to be a spy.

01:05:00.738 --> 01:05:03.730
[ Beeping ]

01:05:03.808 --> 01:05:05.742
You have a name for me.

01:05:05.810 --> 01:05:08.836
[ Carmelo ]
The guy's name is Glenn Harrick.

01:05:08.913 --> 01:05:13.612
He's got a boat on the river
near the 27th Avenue Bridge.

01:05:13.685 --> 01:05:16.017
It cost me a lot of money
to get that information.

01:05:16.087 --> 01:05:18.351
You've just doneyourself
a great favor, Carmelo.

01:05:18.423 --> 01:05:21.358
Doyourself one.
Don't let me seeyou again.

01:05:21.426 --> 01:05:24.589
You take care ofthis guy,
you stay out of myway, we're good.

01:05:24.662 --> 01:05:29.690
- Ifl ever seeyour face again,
I'll kill you-- bomb or no bomb.
- Agreed.

01:05:29.767 --> 01:05:33.168
[Michael]
Oh, look. Theysurvived Nate's exploding truck.

01:05:33.238 --> 01:05:35.536
Think they're keeping Sam here?

01:05:35.607 --> 01:05:37.734
Fits the background
in Sam's photo.

01:05:37.809 --> 01:05:41.643
Lots of rusted metal.
And they probably got him down in the hold.

01:05:41.713 --> 01:05:45.080
Well, it makes sense, a barge.
It's isolated, easy to defend.

01:05:45.149 --> 01:05:47.674
[ Sighs ]
Guess it's time to set my meeting with Harrick.

01:05:47.752 --> 01:05:50.812
- We could go in there now.
- No, Fi.

01:05:50.888 --> 01:05:53.288
- We're gonna do this the right way.
- Boring.

01:05:54.292 --> 01:05:56.658
[Line Ringing]

01:05:56.728 --> 01:05:59.356
- [ Harrick] Yeah.
- I'm ready to make a deal.

01:05:59.430 --> 01:06:01.489
All right.
Let's set it up.

01:06:01.566 --> 01:06:04.899
- I can meet today.
- The girl coming?

01:06:04.969 --> 01:06:07.233
Yeah. I tracked her down.

01:06:07.305 --> 01:06:10.832
F.ine. 4:00.
Be at the Grove Harbour Marina.

01:06:10.908 --> 01:06:14.605
Sounds good. One more thing.
I talk to Sam before I come to the meeting.

01:06:14.679 --> 01:06:18.046
Ifhe can't talk, ifhe doesn't sound healthy,
I walk away.

01:06:18.116 --> 01:06:20.141
Ifhe's anything less
than a hundred percent...

01:06:20.218 --> 01:06:22.379
just kill him now
and save us both some time.

01:06:22.453 --> 01:06:25.047
- We'll take good care ofhim.
- You do that.

01:06:27.725 --> 01:06:29.659
[ Engine Starts ]

01:06:35.166 --> 01:06:37.498
It'll be over today. Hey.

01:06:37.568 --> 01:06:41.231
I was thinkin' about it. Maybeyou should
draw me a picture ofthe map to that park.

01:06:41.306 --> 01:06:43.069
I'm gonna have to
putyour body somewhere.

01:06:43.141 --> 01:06:48.101
Hey. Um, did he ask
to talk to me beforeyou meet?

01:06:48.179 --> 01:06:50.511
'Cause I got news
foryou, buddy.

01:06:50.581 --> 01:06:52.515
I'm not gonna play ball.

01:06:52.583 --> 01:06:55.882
- So you might as well just finish this right now.
- [ Chuckling ]

01:06:55.953 --> 01:06:57.887
You'll do whatever
I wantyou to do.

01:06:57.955 --> 01:07:01.550
But until then,
please, keep him quiet.

01:07:01.626 --> 01:07:03.890
Hey, um, sowhatwereyou?

01:07:03.961 --> 01:07:06.691
Army?I'm a Navyman myself.

01:07:06.764 --> 01:07:09.289
But, you know, I've seen
your boss's type before...

01:07:09.367 --> 01:07:12.063
and whatevershallow grave
he dumps mybodyin...

01:07:12.136 --> 01:07:15.071
you're gonna be keeping me
company there real soon, pal.

01:07:15.139 --> 01:07:17.130
[ Grunts ]

01:07:17.208 --> 01:07:19.608
[ Laughing ]

01:07:19.677 --> 01:07:23.477
You know, I read in a book once
that the things that make you the angriest...

01:07:23.548 --> 01:07:25.573
are the things
you know are true.

01:07:25.650 --> 01:07:30.383
- Wise words, huh?
- I am getting so sick ofyour mouth!

01:07:30.455 --> 01:07:33.788
Take a good look, buddy.
'Cause this is gonna beyou real soon.

01:07:33.858 --> 01:07:35.758
[Sam Laughing]

01:07:39.330 --> 01:07:41.264
[ Laughing Stops ]
Ow.

01:07:43.067 --> 01:07:45.501
Oh, I get it.

01:07:45.570 --> 01:07:48.596
I kill you,
your man doesn't show, right?

01:07:50.308 --> 01:07:53.539
- [ Gun Clicks ]
- Nice try.

01:08:06.557 --> 01:08:10.357
I, uh--
I gotyour buddy's Caddy.

01:08:10.428 --> 01:08:13.693
I had a friend who deals in secondhand cars
check it out. Looks clean.

01:08:13.765 --> 01:08:16.029
He also fixed the windshield
on the Charger.

01:08:16.100 --> 01:08:20.867
- So Mom said thatyou
wanted me to go awaywith her?
- I wantyou two somewhere safe.

01:08:20.938 --> 01:08:23.064
Tell me something.
Why is it, ifyou're the responsible one...

01:08:23.140 --> 01:08:26.474
every timeyou run offand you doyour spy thing,
I gotta pick up the pieces?

01:08:27.545 --> 01:08:30.742
- Please.
- [ Sighs ]

01:08:30.814 --> 01:08:34.307
I like this--
you coming to me for help.

01:08:34.385 --> 01:08:35.875
- It's-- It feels good.
- Yeah.

01:08:35.953 --> 01:08:38.285
- It's like a fresh thing for us, you know?
- It's great.

01:08:38.356 --> 01:08:39.687
- Yeah.
- You gonna do it?

01:08:39.756 --> 01:08:43.124
- Of course, Bro.
- Thanks.

01:08:47.198 --> 01:08:49.564
You'll probably need
a moderate sized blast.

01:08:49.634 --> 01:08:51.658
The metal on that boat
looked prettyworn.

01:08:51.736 --> 01:08:54.170
I'd go with something
with more direction.

01:08:55.372 --> 01:08:56.965
But it'll do.

01:09:13.758 --> 01:09:15.692
[Michael Narrating]
The stickybomb was originally developed...

01:09:15.760 --> 01:09:18.024
in World Warll
formining tanks.

01:09:18.095 --> 01:09:21.689
F.or the homemade variety,
tile adhesive works best.

01:09:21.765 --> 01:09:26.897
Sticky, waterproof, and it comes
in an easilyportable plastic bucket.

01:09:53.798 --> 01:09:57.564
Mom, I'll callyou when--
if it's safe to come back.

01:10:00.705 --> 01:10:03.299
Here, take this.
I t's a new phone.

01:10:03.374 --> 01:10:07.140
I t hasn't been used,
so it's untraceable.

01:10:07.211 --> 01:10:10.647
It's for emergencies only.
We want to keep communication to a minimum.

01:10:10.715 --> 01:10:13.445
